      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ibuprofen and Advil are indeed the same medication, but Tylenol (acetaminophen) is a different class of pain reliever. While Tylenol is often safer for kidney function, you still need to be mindful of the maximum dose, as taking too much can cause liver damage. Please check the dosing recommendations on the packaging and consider if you have any other medications that contain acetaminophen to prevent accidental overdose.",
